Cosatu wants the government to double the COVID-19 relief fund aid but its General Secretary Bheki Ntshalintshali denies reports that the matter was deliberated at the Nedlac meeting with President Cyril Ramaphosa. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cosatu wants the government to double the COVID-19 relief fund aid. Its General Secretary Bheki Ntshalintshali denies reports that the matter was deliberated at the Nedlac meeting with President Cyril Ramaphosa. Workers' Day: Cosatu lauds health workers He spoke during an interview with eNCA's Xoli Mngambi on Monday.
Ntshalintshali said, "in relations to the new budget coming we are hoping that the minister of finance together with the president will be able to inject more stimulus to the economy. READ: Opposition parties react to Ramaphosa's COVID-19 relief plan "The president confirmed that they are doing all they can to put more injection but there was no confirmation whether they will inject R1-trillion that you are referring to." Ntshalintshali said they support safely opening the economy and says there needs to be a balance struck between economic activity and worker safety. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.